+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BVQyBay2B6tUj4VyZpXrhC","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Great! Now I have a comprehensive view. Let me create a final summary document:\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Exploration Summary\n\n### 1. Directory Structure\n\n```\n/workspace/\n├── src/\n│   └── core/\n│       ├── index.ts          (exports)\n│       ├── types.ts          (interfaces)\n│       ├── engine.ts         (BuildEngine class)\n│       └── templates.ts      (template factories)\n│   └── plugins/              (currently empty - to be implemented)\n├── tests/\n│   ├── core.test.ts          (core tests)\n│   └── plugins/\n│       ├── search-index.test.ts\n│       ├── markdown-ext.test.ts\n│       ├── taxonomy.test.ts\n│       ├── dev-server.test.ts\n│       ├── rss-feed.test.ts\n│       ├── sitemap.test.ts\n│       ├── asset-pipeline.test.ts\n│       └── syntax-highlight.test.ts\n├── package.json\n├── tsconfig.json\n└── vitest.config.ts (referenced)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Package.json Details\n\n**Build/Test/Lint Commands:**\n```json\n{\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",                    // TypeScript compilation to ./dist\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",      // ESLint checking\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\"               // Vitest test runner\n  },\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.18.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.18.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.57.1\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.9.3\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.1.9\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@types/express\": \"^5.0.6\",\n    \"@types/marked\": \"^5.0.2\",\n    \"express\": \"^5.2.1\",\n    \"marked\": \"^17.0.2\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. TypeScript Configuration (tsconfig.json)\n\n- **Target:** ES2022\n- **Module System:** Node16\n- **Root Directory:** ./src\n- **Output Directory:** ./dist\n- **Strict Mode:** Enabled\n- **Declaration Files:** Generated\n\n---\n\n### 4. Plugin Interface Definition (src/core/types.ts)\n\n```typescript\nexport interface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];  // names of plugins this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n\nexport interface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n```\n\n**Key Supporting Types:**\n\n```typescript\nexport interface SiteConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  outputDir: string;\n  contentDir: string;\n  templateDir: string;\n}\n\nexport interface ContentFile {\n  slug: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;        // raw content (markdown or html)\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;\n  date?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  template?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;  // output path -> rendered content\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;  // output path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;   // shared plugin data store\n}\n\nexport interface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. BuildEngine Overview (src/core/engine.ts)\n\nThe `BuildEngine` class orchestrates the build process:\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `registerPlugin(plugin: Plugin)` - Add plugins to engine\n- `registerTemplate(template: Template)` - Register rendering templates\n- `resolvePluginOrder(): Plugin[]` - Topological sort using DAG (Directed Acyclic Graph)\n- `build(files: ContentFile[]): Promise<BuildContext>` - Execute full build pipeline\n\n**Build Pipeline Execution Order:**\n1. beforeBuild hooks (in dependency order)\n2. transformContent hooks (applied to each file in plugin order)\n3. Template rendering\n4. afterBuild hooks (in dependency order)\n\n**Dependency Resolution:**\n- Uses depth-first search with cycle detection\n- Throws error on circular dependencies\n- Throws error on missing dependencies\n\n---\n\n### 6. Core Tests (tests/core.test.ts)\n\nTests 17 scenarios covering:\n- Plugin registration and template registration\n- Default and list template rendering\n- Plugin hook execution (beforeBuild, transformContent, afterBuild)\n- Plugin dependency resolution and ordering\n- Circular dependency detection\n- Missing dependency detection\n- Multiple plugin transformation chaining\n- Shared data store functionality\n- File metadata preservation\n- Empty input handling\n\n---\n\n### 7. Plugin Tests - Expected Behaviors\n\n#### **7.1 search-index.test.ts**\n**Purpose:** Generate JSON search index file\n\n**Expected Functionality:**\n- Creates `search-index.json` in ctx.output\n- Index entries contain: slug, title, plain text content\n- HTML tags stripped from content (only text remains)\n- Code blocks included in searchable text\n- Handles empty file lists\n- Valid JSON output\n- Preserves tags if present in metadata\n- Hook used: `afterBuild`\n\n**Example JSON structure:**\n```json\n[\n  { \"slug\": \"my-post\", \"title\": \"My Post\", \"content\": \"Some text here\", \"tags\": [\"js\"] }\n]\n```\n\n---\n\n#### **7.2 markdown-ext.test.ts**\n**Purpose:** Convert markdown to HTML with custom extensions\n\n**Expected Functionality:**\n- Hook used: `transformContent`\n- Converts markdown (# headers, **bold**, etc.) to HTML\n- **Custom extensions:**\n  - Footnotes: `[^1]` syntax → `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>`\n  - Footnote section: renders at bottom in `<section class=\"footnotes\">`\n  - Admonition containers:\n    - `:::note` → `<div class=\"admonition admonition-note\">`\n    - `:::warning` → `<div class=\"admonition admonition-warning\">`\n    - `:::tip` → `<div class=\"admonition admonition-tip\">`\n- Preserves existing HTML content\n- Handles empty content gracefully\n\n---\n\n#### **7.3 taxonomy.test.ts**\n**Purpose:** Build tag-based taxonomy and generate tag pages\n\n**Expected Functionality:**\n- Hooks used: `beforeBuild`, `afterBuild`\n- `beforeBuild`: builds tag map from file.tags\n  - Stores in ctx.data as Map keyed 'taxonomy-tags'\n  - Key structure: Map<string (normalized tag), ContentFile[]>\n  - Tags normalized to lowercase\n- `afterBuild`: generates tag listing pages\n  - Files in format: `tags/{tagname}.html`\n  - Each page lists all files with that tag (includes title)\n  - Handles files with no tags\n  - Handles multiple tags per file\n  - Handles empty file list\n\n---\n\n#### **7.4 dev-server.test.ts**\n**Purpose:** Configure development server\n\n**Expected Functionality:**\n- Hook used: `afterBuild`\n- Stores dev-server-config in ctx.data (key: 'dev-server-config')\n- Config structure:\n  ```typescript\n  {\n    port: number;\n    routes: Array<{ path: string; handler: string }>;\n    assetPaths: string[];\n    searchIndexPath: string;\n  }\n  ```\n- Default port: 3000\n- Asset routes from asset-pipeline plugin's 'asset-manifest'\n  - Handler type: 'asset'\n- Search index path: '/search-index.json' (if exists in ctx.output)\n- Content routes for HTML files\n  - Handler type: 'static'\n- Gracefully handles missing asset-pipeline data\n\n---\n\n#### **7.5 rss-feed.test.ts**\n**Purpose:** Generate RSS 2.0 XML feed\n\n**Expected Functionality:**\n- Hook used: `afterBuild`\n- Generates `feed.xml` in ctx.output\n- Valid RSS 2.0 XML structure: `<?xml version=\"1.0\"...` and `<rss version=\"2.0\">`\n- Uses channel and item elements\n- Feed items contain:\n  - Title\n  - HTML content wrapped in CDATA: `<![CDATA[...]]>`\n  - Categories from tags (if available from taxonomy plugin)\n  - Publication date (if exists)\n- Channel title from config.title\n- Channel link from config.baseUrl\n- Item links: `{baseUrl}/{slug}.html`\n- Items sorted by date, newest first\n- Handles files without dates (no undefined pubDate)\n\n---\n\n#### **7.6 sitemap.test.ts**\n**Purpose:** Generate XML sitemap for SEO\n\n**Expected Functionality:**\n- Hook used: `afterBuild`\n- Generates `sitemap.xml` in ctx.output\n- Valid XML structure: `<?xml version=\"1.0\"...`, `<urlset>`, `<url>`, `<loc>`\n- URLs include:\n  - All content HTML files from ctx.output (e.g., post-1.html)\n  - Tag pages from taxonomy (e.g., tags/javascript.html)\n  - Feed file (feed.xml)\n- All URLs prefixed with config.baseUrl\n- Handles sites without tag pages\n- Example URL format: `https://example.com/post-1.html`\n\n---\n\n#### **7.7 asset-pipeline.test.ts**\n**Purpose:** Manage static assets (images, documents, etc.)\n\n**Expected Functionality:**\n- Hook used: `transformContent`\n- Rewrites relative asset URLs to `/assets/` path:\n  - `src=\"./image.png\"` → `src=\"/assets/image.png\"`\n  - `href=\"./doc.pdf\"` → `href=\"/assets/doc.pdf\"`\n- Leaves absolute URLs unchanged (http/https)\n- Already rewritten URLs not double-processed\n- Generates asset-manifest in ctx.data\n  - Key: 'asset-manifest'\n  - Structure: `{ assets: string[] }` (filenames like 'photo.jpg')\n- Accumulates assets across multiple files\n- Handles files with no asset references\n\n---\n\n#### **7.8 syntax-highlight.test.ts**\n**Purpose:** Add syntax highlighting metadata to code blocks\n\n**Expected Functionality:**\n- Hook used: `transformContent`\n- Targets: `<pre><code class=\"language-*\">` blocks\n- Transformations:\n  - Adds `highlighted` class to code tag\n  - Adds `data-language` attribute to pre tag with extracted language\n  - Example: `class=\"language-javascript\"` → `class=\"language-javascript highlighted\"` + `<pre data-language=\"javascript\">`\n- Handles multiple code blocks in one file\n- Skips code blocks without language specified (no class=\"language-*\")\n- Preserves code block content\n- Handles empty code blocks (still adds attributes)\n- Does not modify inline code tags (outside `<pre>`)\n\n---\n\n### 8. Build Pipeline Summary\n\nThe SSG (Static Site Generator) processes content through this flow:\n\n```\nInput Files → Plugins (beforeBuild) \n           → Plugins (transformContent) \n           → Template Rendering \n           → Plugins (afterBuild) \n           → Output\n```\n\n**Plugin Execution Order:** Determined by dependency graph (topological sort)\n\n**Shared Context:** `BuildContext` passed to all hooks, allowing plugins to:\n- Read site config\n- Access all files\n- Share data via `ctx.data` Map\n- Generate binary assets\n- Produce output files\n\n---\n\n### Key Implementation Notes\n\n1. **Plugin dependencies are declared** - enables ordering, circular detection\n2. **Hooks can be async or sync** - flexible execution model\n3. **All hooks are optional** - plugins only implement what they need\n4. **Shared data store** - plugins communicate via ctx.data\n5. **Two output maps** - text content (ctx.output) and binary assets (ctx.assets)\n6. **File transformation** - each plugin gets full file object to read/modify\n7. **Template system** - separates content from presentation\n8. **Marked library imported** - available for markdown-ext plugin\n9. **Express available** - available for dev-server plugin (development mode)\n\n---\n\nThis structure implements a flexible, DAG-based plugin system for building static sites with markdown transformation, asset management, SEO features (sitemap/RSS), and development server integration."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a3019af (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 34130\ntool_uses: 19\nduration_ms: 38136</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d306d236-3f8c-4389-953f-cdf19a4168e1","uuid":"60a619e9-a5a0-4596-9f3d-d19a2762d138","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase structure thoroughly. I need to understand:\n1. The overall directory layout\n2. The contents of src/core/ (types, build engine, templates)\n3. The Plugin interface from src/core/types.ts\n4. The existing tests in tests/core.test.ts\n5. All test files in tests/plugins