s existing HTML content\n- Handles empty content gracefully\n\n---\n\n#### **7.3 taxonomy.test.ts**\n**Purpose:** Build tag-based taxonomy and generate tag pages\n\n**Expected Functionality:**\n- Hooks used: `beforeBuild`, `afterBuild`\n- `beforeBuild`: builds tag map from file.tags\n  - Stores in ctx.data as Map keyed 'taxonomy-tags'\n  - Key structure: Map<string (normalized tag), ContentFile[]>\n  - Tags normalized to lowercase\n- `afterBuild`: generates tag listing pages\n  - Files in format: `tags/{tagname}.html`\n  - Each page lists all files with that tag (includes title)\n  - Handles files with no tags\n  - Handles multiple tags per file\n  - Handles empty file list\n\n---\n\n#### **7.4 dev-server.test.ts**\n**Purpose:** Configure development server\n\n**Expected Functionality:**\n- Hook used: `afterBuild`\n- Stores dev-server-config in ctx.data (key: 'dev-server-config')\n- Config structure:\n  ```typescript\n  {\n    port: number;\n    routes: Array<{ path: string; handler: string }>;\n    assetPaths: string[];\n    searchIndexPath: string;\n  }\n  ```\n- Default port: 3000\n- Asset routes from asset-pipeline plugin's 'asset-manifest'\n  - Handler type: 'asset'\n- Search index path: '/search-index.json' (if exists in ctx.output)\n- Content routes for HTML files\n  - Handler type: 'static'\n- Gracefully handles missing asset-pipeline data\n\n---\n\n#### **7.5 rss-feed.test.ts**\n**Purpose:** Generate RSS 2.0 XML feed\n\n**Expected Functionality:**\n- Hook used: `afterBuild`\n- Generates `feed.xml` in ctx.output\n- Valid RSS 2.0 XML structure: `<?xml version=\"1.0\"...` and `<rss version=\"2.0\">`\n- Uses channel and item elements\n- Feed items contain:\n  - Title\n  - HTML content wrapped in CDATA: `<![CDATA[...]]>`\n  - Categories from tags (if available from taxonomy plugin)\n  - Publication date (if exists)\n- Channel title from config.title\n- Channel link from config.baseUrl\n- Item links: `{baseUrl}/{slug}.html`\n- Items sorted by date, newest first\n- Handles files without dates (no undefined pubDate)\n\n---\n\n#### **7.6 sitemap.test.ts**\n**Purpose:** Generate XML sitemap for SEO\n\n**Expected Functionality:**\n- Hook used: `afterBuild`\n- Generates `sitemap.xml` in ctx.output\n- Valid XML structure: `<?xml version=\"1.0\"...`, `<urlset>`, `<url>`, `<loc>`\n- URLs include:\n  - All content HTML files from ctx.output (e.g., post-1.html)\n  - Tag pages from taxonomy (e.g., tags/javascript.html)\n  - Feed file (feed.xml)\n- All URLs prefixed with config.baseUrl\n- Handles sites without tag pages\n- Example URL format: `https://example.com/post-1.html`\n\n---\n\n#### **7.7 asset-pipeline.test.ts**\n**Purpose:** Manage static assets (images, documents, etc.)\n\n**Expected Functionality:**\n- Hook used: `transformContent`\n- Rewrites relative asset URLs to `/assets/` path:\n  - `src=\"./image.png\"` → `src=\"/assets/image.png\"`\n  - `href=\"./doc.pdf\"` → `href=\"/assets/doc.pdf\"`\n- Leaves absolute URLs unchanged (http/https)\n- Already rewritten URLs not double-processed\n- Generates asset-manifest in ctx.data\n  - Key: 'asset-manifest'\n  - Structure: `{ assets: string[] }` (filenames like 'photo.jpg')\n- Accumulates assets across multiple files\n- Handles files with no asset references\n\n---\n\n#### **7.8 syntax-highlight.test.ts**\n**Purpose:** Add syntax highlighting metadata to code blocks\n\n**Expected Functionality:**\n- Hook used: `transformContent`\n- Targets: `<pre><code class=\"language-*\">` blocks\n- Transformations:\n  - Adds `highlighted` class to code tag\n  - Adds `data-language` attribute to pre tag with extracted language\n  - Example: `class=\"language-javascript\"` → `class=\"language-javascript highlighted\"` + `<pre data-language=\"javascript\">`\n- Handles multiple code blocks in one file\n- Skips code blocks without language specified (no class=\"language-*\")\n- Preserves code block content\n- Handles empty code blocks (still adds attributes)\n- Does not modify inline code tags (outside `<pre>`)\n\n---\n\n### 8. Build Pipeline Summary\n\nThe SSG (Static Site Generator) processes content through this flow:\n\n```\nInput Files → Plugins (beforeBuild) \n           → Plugins (transformContent) \n           → Template Rendering \n           → Plugins (afterBuild) \n           → Output\n```\n\n**Plugin Execution Order:** Determined by dependency graph (topological sort)\n\n**Shared Context:** `BuildContext` passed to all hooks, allowing plugins to:\n- Read site config\n- Access all files\n- Share data via `ctx.data` Map\n- Generate binary assets\n- Produce output files\n\n---\n\n### Key Implementation Notes\n\n1. **Plugin dependencies are declared** - enables ordering, circular detection\n2. **Hooks can be async or sync** - flexible execution model\n3. **All hooks are optional** - plugins only implement what they need\n4. **Shared data store** - plugins communicate via ctx.data\n5. **Two output maps** - text content (ctx.output) and binary assets (ctx.assets)\n6. **File transformation** - each plugin gets full file object to read/modify\n7. **Template system** - separates content from presentation\n8. **Marked library imported** - available for markdown-ext plugin\n9. **Express available** - available for dev-server plugin (development mode)\n\n---\n\nThis structure implements a flexible, DAG-based plugin system for building static sites with markdown transformation, asset management, SEO features (sitemap/RSS), and development server integration."}],"totalDurationMs":38136,"totalTokens":34130,"totalToolUseCount":19,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":220,"cache_read_input_tokens":30767,"output_tokens":3140,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":220,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[]}}}
